<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[154, 106, 920, 141]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[154, 463, 655, 483]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>equation<|/ref|><|det|>[[379, 500, 620, 534]]<|/det|>

<mark>[4]

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[116, 133, 341, 151]]<|/det|>

<label>(a)</label>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[154, 198, 707, 234]]<|/det|>

<label>(a)</label>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[154, 163, 534, 182]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[114, 170, 146, 188]]<|/det|>
<label>(a)</label>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[154, 170, 240, 188]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>equation<|/ref|><|det|>[[373, 189, 623, 222]]<|/det|>

<mark>[4]

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[114, 72, 146, 88]]<|/det|>
<label>(b)</label>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[154, 72, 507, 88]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[114, 72, 144, 89]]<|/det|>
<label>(a)</label>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[154, 71, 792, 91]]<|/det|>
Starting from the definitions of \(\tanh\) and \(\operatorname{sech}\) in terms of exponentials, prove that

<|ref|>equation<|/ref|><|det|>[[415, 100, 583, 121]]<|/det|>
\[1 - \tanh^{2}x = \operatorname {sech}^{2}x. \]

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[890, 101, 920, 120]]<|/det|>
<mark>[3]

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[111, 320, 143, 339]]<|/det|>
<label>(b)</label>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[154, 316, 720, 344]]<|/det|>
Using the substitution \(u = \tanh x\), or otherwise, find \(\int \operatorname {sech}^{2}x\tanh^{2}x \mathrm{~d}x\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[890, 320, 920, 339]]<|/det|>
<mark>[2]

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[111, 567, 536, 593]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[154, 598, 326, 617]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>equation<|/ref|><|det|>[[356, 621, 641, 653]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[890, 625, 920, 644]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[154, 670, 611, 698]]<|/det|>
